            .eight.columns.fadeInDown
                //- h1.u So... what is iGEM Toronto?
                h5.black University of Toronto iGEM (International Genetically Engineered Machine) is a student association dedicated to the practice of synthetic biology and dissemination of its scientific foundations. Every year our team designs and executes a synthetic biology research project, and joins teams from across the world to compete at the iGEM Grand Jamboree conference in Boston, Massachusetts, USA in November.
        .row.margin.container-fluid.bc-white-pattern.fadeInDownP
            .eight.columns.fadeInDown
                h1.u What do we do?
                p <br>
                p <br>
                h5 Outside of the competition, the iGEM Toronto club is an interdisciplinary space for those interested in synthetic biology to learn more about the field by participating in engaging seminars and design sessions.
                h5 We are currently in the process of developing our 2017 project, and expect to begin recruitment in mid-march.  Stay tuned on our facebook page for more updates regarding our events and recruitment sessions or contact us at igem@g.skule.ca for more info.
